@startuml
autonumber
actor "Prosumer Asset" as Asset
box "Orchestration Layer" #LightCyan
participant "Camunda Engine" as Camunda
participant "Kong Gateway" as Kong
end box
box "Messaging Layer" #Thistle
queue "Kafka Topic:\n{AssetLinkID}-{UtilityOperator}" as KafkaIn
queue "Kafka Topic:\nDashboard Metrics" as KafkaOut
end box
box "Microservice Layer" #LightYellow
participant "Telemetry MS" as TelemetryMS
participant "Energy Analytics MS" as AnalyticsMS
end box
box "Persistence Layer" #LightGreen
database "AWS RDS\n(Telemetry DB)" as TelemetryDB
end box

== High-Frequency Telemetry Ingestion ==

Asset -> KafkaIn: Publish JSON Payload
note right: Payloads are (BATTERY, SOLAR, EV_CHARGER).\nPartitioned by asset_id to guarantee chronological order.

loop continuous polling
    TelemetryMS -> KafkaIn: consume from Topic: 'assetId-ZoneId'
    KafkaIn --> TelemetryMS: JSON Payload
end

TelemetryMS -> TelemetryDB: JDBC INSERT Time-Series Metrics\n(asset_id, grid_cell_id, asset_type, payload, timestamp)
TelemetryDB --> TelemetryMS: 200 OK

== Scheduled Energy Analytics ==

Camunda -> Kong: Trigger Analytics Batch
Kong --> AnalyticsMS: Forward Request
AnalyticsMS -> TelemetryDB: JDBC Query raw telemetry batch\n(asset_id, grid_cell_id, soc_percent,\nenergy readings, timestamp)
TelemetryDB --> AnalyticsMS: 200 OK {telemetryRecords[]}
AnalyticsMS -> AnalyticsMS: Calculate KPIs
AnalyticsMS -> KafkaOut: Publish KPI Results
note right: Four dedicated topics are produced:\n- Energy-Discharged-By-Zone\n- Generated-Energy-By-Prosumer\n- Consumed-Energy-By-Prosumer\n- Average-SoC
KafkaOut --> AnalyticsMS: Ack
AnalyticsMS --> Kong: Analytics Complete
Kong --> Camunda: Analytics Complete
@enduml